{
  "text": "In this study, we screened the effects of the arabinogalactan against the experimental models of gastric hypersecretion, ulcer, and gastrointestinal motility in which Maytenus ilicifolia, from which this compound has been isolated, showed potent gastroprotective activity. Isolation and identifi cation of the AG has been described in detail elsewhere [CITATION_1] . The content of this purifi ed AG in M. ilicifolia was 0.38% w/w and its average molar mass (M) was 11400 g/mol.",
  "citation_candidates": [
